{
  "texts": [
    "We hypothesize that bread wheat landraces with higher L3 genome content, possibly representing a more ancestral state of the L3 introgression(s), have been preserved in ex situ collections but are rare and geographically restricted.",
    "To identify bread wheat accessions with above-average proportions of L3 genome, we developed the 'Missing Link Finder' pipeline (Fig. 3a).",
    "Missing Link Finder estimates the similarity between a species-or lineage-specific reference k-mer set and sample k-mer sets generated from genotyping data of individual wheat accessions, computing the result as Jaccard similarity coefficients.",
    "To deploy Missing Link Finder, we used a reference k-mer set consisting of 769 million Ae.",
    "tauschii L3-specific k-mers 14 and compared it to individual sample k-mer sets from 82,293 genotyped wheat accessions (6.16 million k-mers per ATG 1,202 bp 4,028 bp 1 kb 100 aa LrSi2 LrSi6 R457I C1023S Kinase 1 Kinase 2 MSP W D40 TAA AL8/78 TA1675 BSMV-γGFP BSMV-γGFP BSMV-γLrSi2 BSMV-γLrSi3 BSMV-γLrSi6 BSMV-γLrSi7 BSMV-γLrSi8 d c 10.0 9.5 9.0 8.5 8.0 7.5 7.0 6.5 6.0 9.0 8.5 8.0 7.5 7.0 6.5 6.0 1.2 2.8 1.8 2.6 2.4 2.2 2.0 1.6"
  ]
}